---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { BASE_URL, REPO, ROADMAP, COMPETITIVE } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Investors — osx-ide"
  description="A native macOS AI IDE redefining developer productivity. Local-first AI, cloud-scale orchestration, and enterprise-grade privacy."
  canonical={`${BASE_URL}/investors`}
>
  <section class="page-hero" style="text-align:center">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="section-kicker reveal">For investors</p>
      <h1 class="reveal text-gradient">Redefining AI development on macOS</h1>
      <p class="reveal" style="font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--text-dim);max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.7">
        Every AI IDE today is a browser wrapper that sends your code to a cloud server for every keystroke.
        osx-ide is built from the ground up on a different premise — and that premise is a business opportunity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="reveal" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin-bottom:48px">
        <div class="card" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px">
          <div class="hero-stat-value text-gradient">$30B+</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">AI code assistant TAM by 2028</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px">
          <div class="hero-stat-value text-gradient">5×</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">Faster latencies than cloud-only</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px">
          <div class="hero-stat-value text-gradient">100%</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">Privacy by default (local-first)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:16px;font-weight:600">The problem</h2>
      <p class="reveal" style="font-size:.92rem;color:var(--text-dim);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:32px">
        Current AI IDEs (Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf) are cloud-only by design. Every keystroke, every prompt, every completion
        requires a round-trip to a remote server. This means <strong>500–2000ms latency</strong> for autocomplete,
        <strong>zero offline capability</strong>, <strong>no privacy guarantee</strong> for enterprise IP, and a
        <strong>$15–20/mo per-seat tax</strong> regardless of whether users actually need cloud models for every interaction.
      </p>

      <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:16px;font-weight:600">Our moat</h2>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;margin-bottom:32px">
        <div class="reveal card">
          <h3 style="font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--cyan)">Dual-pipeline architecture</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--text-dim)">Local (<strong>&lt;100ms</strong>, 4B MLX, offline) and cloud (orchestration graph, 20+ tools, RAG) pipelines share zero AI execution code. Each is independently optimized. This is not a feature switch — it's a deep architectural decision that competitors cannot retroactively match without a rewrite.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal card">
          <h3 style="font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--cyan)">Native Apple Silicon</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--text-dim)">SwiftUI + AppKit, not Electron. MLX for on-device inference. Metal acceleration. osx-ide uses Apple Silicon as a first-class AI compute platform, not a thin client for someone else's server.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal card">
          <h3 style="font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--cyan)">Business model aligned with architecture</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--text-dim)">The local pipeline is free and open source. The cloud pipeline is usage-based, not per-seat. Organizations pay only when they use cloud AI. This makes adoption frictionless and scales naturally with usage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal card">
          <h3 style="font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--cyan)">Privacy by design</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--text-dim)">Enterprise IP never leaves the endpoint without explicit consent. Compliance-ready from day one — not patched in later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:16px;font-weight:600">Roadmap to commercial deployment</h2>
      <div class="roadmap-strip reveal" style="margin-bottom:32px">
        {ROADMAP.map((phase) => (
          <div class="roadmap-phase">
            <h3>{phase.phase}</h3>
            <ul>
              {phase.items.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin-bottom:16px;font-weight:600">Contact</h2>
      <p class="reveal" style="font-size:.92rem;color:var(--text-dim);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:8px">
        For qualified investor inquiries, please reach out via the repository or email.
        We are currently in closed beta and preparing the commercial tier.
      </p>
      <div class="reveal" style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={`${BASE_URL}/beta`}>Join closed beta</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={REPO} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View source</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
